# LoRaLink Coding Style & AI Rules

## C++ Coding Standards
- **Indentation:** 2 spaces.
- **Braces:** Same line for `if`, `for`, `while`, `switch`.
- **Naming:**
  - Classes: `PascalCase` (e.g., `DataManager`).
  - Functions: `camelCase` (e.g., `handlePacket`).
  - Variables: `camelCase` (e.g., `lastUpdate`).
  - Constants/Macros: `UPPER_CASE` (e.g., `PIN_LORA_CS`).
- **Singleton Pattern:** Always use `static T& getInstance()` and private constructor.

## AI Assistant Guidelines
- ALWAYS check `CLAUDE.md` and `AGENTS.md` before starting work.
- Use `LOG_PRINTLN` and `LOG_PRINTF` from `utils/DebugMacros.h` instead of raw `Serial.println`.
- Never suggest code that instantiates a singleton Manager directly.
- Ensure all headers have loop guards.
- When adding new Manager files, update `CLAUDE.md` architecture section.

## CommInterface Rules
- Never use `SERIAL` (collides with Arduino core). Use `COMM_SERIAL`.
- Ensure all switch statements handling `CommInterface` have a `default:` case.
